.TH NOVA 1 "April 2026" "nova" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
nova \- terminal panel for amateur astronomers
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B nova
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B nova
is a terminal panel showing weather forecast, ephemeris, astronomical
events, and sky imagery, designed to help amateur astronomers decide
whether it is worth setting up the telescope tonight.
.PP
Rust feature port of astropanel. Built on Crust. Shares the ephemeris
engine with Tock.
.SH FIRST RUN
On first launch, nova prompts interactively for:
.IP \[bu] 2
Display location name
.IP \[bu] 2
IANA timezone (Cont/City) for the events feed
.IP \[bu] 2
Latitude and longitude
.IP \[bu] 2
UTC offset in hours
.IP \[bu] 2
Observation limits (cloud, humidity, temp, wind)
.IP \[bu] 2
Bortle scale for your site
.PP
Responses are saved to
.IR ~/.nova/config.yml
and can be re-edited from the running app (see KEYS).
.SH PANES
.TP
.B Header (row 1)
Column legend and body symbols, location, timezone, lat/lon, Bortle,
last-updated time, and current Julian Date.
.TP
.B Titles (row 2)
Limit markers (<40% cloud, <80% humidity, >-10°C temperature, <8m/s
wind), column ruler for the 9 bodies, selected date/weekday/hour,
and current moon phase name + illumination percent.
.TP
.B Left pane
Hourly weather rows for the next ~9 days. Each row is color-coded
green/yellow/red by condition score, followed by a visibility-bar
column for each of Sun, Moon, Mercury, Venus, Mars, Jupiter, Saturn,
Uranus, Neptune. Moon bar intensity tracks phase illumination.
An exclamation mark on a row indicates an astronomical event in that
hour bracket.
.TP
.B Main pane
Weather detail for the selected hour, full ephemeris table, the
event description (colored by condition), and the starchart / APOD
image when available.
.TP
.B Footer
Keybinding hint bar.
.SH KEYS
.TP
.B ?
Show help overlay.
.TP
.B UP / DOWN
Move selection by one hour.
.TP
.B PgUP / PgDOWN
Move by one page.
.TP
.B HOME / END
Jump to first / last hour.
.TP
.B ENTER
Refresh the currently displayed image (starchart or APOD).
.TP
.B r
Redraw all panes.
.TP
.B R
Refetch weather + events (bypasses cache).
.TP
.B l
Edit location name.
.TP
.B a
Edit latitude.
.TP
.B o
Edit longitude.
.TP
.B c
Edit cloud limit.
.TP
.B h
Edit humidity limit.
.TP
.B t
Edit lower temperature limit.
.TP
.B w
Edit wind limit.
.TP
.B b
Edit Bortle scale.
.TP
.B e
Show all upcoming events in the main pane.
.TP
.B s
Fetch starchart for the selected hour (lat > 23 only).
.TP
.B S
Open the starchart JPG in the system image viewer (xdg-open).
.TP
.B A
Show Astronomy Picture of the Day.
.TP
.B W
Save config to disk.
.TP
.B q
Quit.
.SH CONDITION SCORING
Each hour row is given "negative points":
.IP \[bu] 2
+2 if cloud cover > cloud_limit
.IP \[bu] 2
+1 if cloud cover > (100 - cloud_limit)/2
.IP \[bu] 2
+1 if cloud cover > 90%
.IP \[bu] 2
+1 if humidity > humidity_limit
.IP \[bu] 2
+1 if temperature < temp_limit
.IP \[bu] 2
+1 if temperature < temp_limit - 7\u{00B0}C
.IP \[bu] 2
+1 if wind > wind_limit
.IP \[bu] 2
+1 if wind > 2 * wind_limit
.PP
0-1 points = GOOD (green), 2-3 = FAIR (yellow), 4+ = BAD (red).
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.nova/config.yml
User configuration.
.TP
.I ~/.nova/weather_cache.json
Cached weather forecast (3-hour TTL).
.TP
.I ~/.nova/images/
Cached APOD (per UTC day) and starchart images (per date/hour/location).
.SH DATA SOURCES
.IP \[bu] 2
Weather: api.met.no (Norwegian Meteorological Institute)
.IP \[bu] 2
Events: in-the-sky.org RSS feed
.IP \[bu] 2
Starchart: stelvision.com
.IP \[bu] 2
APOD: apod.nasa.gov
.IP \[bu] 2
Ephemeris: IAU 2006 obliquity standard, ported from ruby-ephemeris.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B HOME
Base for the \fI~/.nova\fR config and cache directory.
